.TH KINDLETOOL 1 "July 2026" "KindleTool 2.0.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
kindletool \- inspect, verify, extract, and create Kindle update packages
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B kindletool
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
KindleTool 2.0 is a Rust implementation of the Kindle v1.6.6 disk formats with a deliberately
new command line. It recognizes FB01, FB02, FB03, FC02, FC04, FD03, FD04, FL01, SP01, CB01,
gzip, and ZIP. It never implicitly deletes input packages.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B inspect package [--format human|json]
Parse metadata without implying that content or signatures are valid.
.TP
.B verify package [--policy structural|authentic] [--format human|json]
Check SP01, payload digest, archive paths, manifest, file hashes and signatures, plus optional
device, firmware, platform and board targets. The default policy is authentic.
.TP
.B extract package directory [--policy structural|authentic]
Verify before atomically committing a staged extraction. The default policy is structural.
.TP
.B export payload --view decoded|stored package --output file
Export an explicit payload representation. A single dash writes staged output to stdout.
.TP
.B export signature package --output file
Export the SP01 signature.
.TP
.B export inner package --output file
Remove exactly one SP01 envelope.
.TP
.B create ota-v1|ota-v2|recovery-v1|recovery-v2|userdata [options] input...
Create and self-verify one package. Output is mandatory with
.BR --output .
Use
.B --archive
for a prebuilt archive; positional arguments are otherwise archive inputs.
.TP
.B codec mangle|demangle input --output file
Apply or reverse the Kindle byte substitution.
.TP
.B serial serial-number
Print model information and derived root/recovery passwords.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 indicates success or Accepted, 1 Rejected, 2 command-line usage failure, and 3 execution error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B KT_WITH_UNKNOWN_DEVCODES
Allow data-mined device codes while expanding create aliases.
.TP
.B TMPDIR
Select temporary spooling storage.
.SH SAFETY
Archive verification rejects absolute paths, parent traversal, duplicate paths, escaping links,
unsupported entries, manifest mismatches, invalid hashes and required invalid signatures. Output
files and extraction directories are staged, flushed, verified, and committed only on success.
.SH COMPATIBILITY
The legacy md, dm, convert, info, version, and help subcommands are not accepted. See
docs/migration-2.0.md. The C v1.6.6 implementation remains the differential-test oracle.
.SH LICENSE
GPL-3.0-or-later.
